@Strickalator @valedinapoli @elonmusk @poisonouspinups @michael_saylor @Bitcoin @dogecoin When buying crypto, the market cap is important, as are a number of other things. For people serious about profiting, the individual unit price is meaningless.

@Strickalator @valedinapoli @elonmusk @poisonouspinups @michael_saylor @Bitcoin @dogecoin A lot of retail crypto buyers look at coins that are individually cheap and think they have a lot of room to grow, not realising they have already grown and there are about 10000x more of them than there are bitcoin.

@Strickalator @valedinapoli @elonmusk @poisonouspinups @michael_saylor @Bitcoin @dogecoin Ok, sincerely. The unit price is irrelevant. BTC is divisible. You can buy $10 of it or $500. It is broken down into Satoshis.
